What is agent-orchestra? <p>Agent-orchestra is a cutting-edge project designed to streamline and manage multiple agents or services within a unified framework. It leverages technologies like TypeScript, Python, and Docker to provide a robust and scalable solution for users. The project aims to simplify the orchestration of various agents, making it easier to manage and monitor their performance.</p> How do I install agent-orchestra? <p>To install agent-orchestra, follow these steps:</p> <ol> <li>Ensure you have Docker installed on your system. You can download it from https://www.docker.com/products/docker-desktop.</li> <li>Clone the agent-orchestra repository from GitHub using the command:    ```bash git clone https://github.com/your-username/agent-orchestra.git <pre><code>3. Navigate to the cloned repository:
   ```bash
cd agent-orchestra
</code></pre></li> <li>Build the Docker image:    ```bash docker build -t agent-orchestra . <pre><code>5. Run the Docker container:
   ```bash
docker run -p 8080:8080 agent-orchestra
</code></pre> Your agent-orchestra instance should now be accessible on port 8080.</li> </ol> What is the basic usage of agent-orchestra? <p>The basic usage of agent-orchestra involves creating and managing agents. Here's a simple example:</p> <ol> <li>Create a new agent configuration file in YAML format. For instance, <code>agent1.yaml</code>:    ```yml name: Agent 1 type: example <pre><code>2. Use the agent-orchestra CLI to start the agent:
   ```bash
orchestra start agent1.yaml
</code></pre></li> <li>You can monitor the agent's status and logs through the agent-orchestra dashboard or CLI.</li> </ol> How do I configure agent-orchestra? <p>Configuration in agent-orchestra is primarily done through YAML files. Here's an example configuration file:    ```yml agents:   - name: Agent 1     type: example     settings:       param1: value1       param2: value2 <pre><code>You can specify multiple agents and their configurations within the same file. For advanced configurations, refer to the [project documentation](https://agent-orchestra.readthedocs.io/en/latest/configuration.html).

